title: Dani Dyer is 'definitely' up for taking part in I'm A Celebrity
text:
Her profile has skyrocketed since she won Love Island in 2018.

And Dani Dyer now wants to compete with other stars in the jungle as she revealed she is 'definitely' up for I'm A Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here!

The reality star, 23, is keen to take part in another reality contest and an encounter with creepy crawlies and bushtucker trials on the hit jungle show is her choice.

New challenge: Dani Dyer now wants to compete with other stars in the jungle as she revealed she is 'definitely' up for I'm A Celebrity... Get Me Out Of Here!

Dani told The Daily Star: 'One I would definitely do is probably go to the jungle.

'I think I'd really struggle with the food.

'I feel like you can never say never to things, it just depends where you are.'

The Love Island winner joked that her mother Joanne Mas is on board with the proposed venture because she would like 'three weeks holiday' at the show's hotel.

Familiar face: The reality star, 23, is keen to take part in another reality contest and an encounter with creepy crawlies and bushtucker trials on the hit jungle show is her choice (I'm A Celeb hosts Ant and Dec pictured in 2017)

Up for it: Dani told The Daily Star : 'One I would definitely do is probably go to the jungle. I think I'd really struggle with the food.' (pictured in September)

Dani also said 'never say never' to the prospect of joining her father Danny in EastEnders too.

Dani won ITV's Love Island with ex beau Jack Fincham and the pair embarked on an off-screen romance before splitting up earlier this year.

She has since rekindled her romance with former flame Sammy Kimmence, a 23-year-old stockbroker who also grew up in Essex.

Family affair: Dani also said 'never say never' to the prospect of joining her father Danny in EastEnders too (pictured together in September)

In July Dani revealed that she sought the help of a psychiatrist after struggling to cope with the fame and attention Love Island brought her in a candid interview.

Speaking to Stella magazine, the reality star opened up about the aftermath of living in the famous villa, with the months following also seeing the breakdown of her relationship with Jack.

She admitted to the publication: 'It can be very tough. I spoke to a psychologist from the show before I went on and afterwards. I had several calls from the producers checking if I was OK.'

Short-lived: Dani won ITV's Love Island with Jack Fincham and the pair embarked on an off-screen romance before splitting up earlier this year (pictured in July)

'And a few weeks after the show, when I felt overwhelmed and said I needed to speak to someone, they put me in touch with a psychiatrist.'

I'm A Celebrity will return to TV screens next month.

Among the rumoured contests are Nadine Coyle, Lucy Fallon, Olivia Attwood and Jacqueline Jossa.

This year's show will see Ant McPartlin returning as Dec's co-host after Holly Willoughby stood in for him following his drink-driving hiatus.
